  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Sukhdev Yadav @ Pehalwan versus State of (NCT of Delhi) & Others pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_7_2012_2052','2025INSC969'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SUKHDEV YADAV @ PEHALWAN<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF (NCT OF DELHI) & OTHERS </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 2012</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 969</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008282025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : B.V. NAGARATHNA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, K.V. VISWANATHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether, an accused/convict who has completed his &ldquo;life imprisonment for a fixed term&rdquo; such as twenty years of actual sentence without remission, as in the instant case, is entitled to be released from prison on completion of such a sentence or in other of the fixed term of sentence as aforesaid, should the accused/convict seek remission of his sentence of &ldquo;life imprisonment&rdquo; by making an application to the competent authority for seeking &ldquo;reduction of his sentence&rdquo;. Headnotes&dagger; Penal Code, 1860 &ndash; ss.53,<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 29-07-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 3271/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_7_2012_2052','2025INSC969','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a